snippet.textDisplay: They ruined a really good song by Mussarat Nazir. The poor lady Mussarat Nazir sang only one good song throughout her life, and Shuja Haider thought a crazy idea to convert it into a rock track. Since all the other songs in this episode are even worse, this song had a chance to shine. Naeem Rufi is a failed artist so it is okay for him to sing whatever comes his way, but I didn't expect this from Meesha. They didn't even try to correct the lyrics before singing it, horrible. This year's coke studio is no better than its crappy Indian counterpart. I thought Strings were doing it terribly for the last 2 years and someone else would improve it, but this time is the worst ever.
